23/01/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Ion Iliescu received the 2002 annual award for Best Politician at a ceremony organised by the daily <I>Nine o'Clock</I> on Wednesday (22 January). The panel of journalists voted on the basis of the following criteria: pursuing a policy of national reconciliation, conducting open dialogue with all political forces, sustained involvement in the fight against corruption, and poverty reduction. Radu Bogdan, chairman of the jury and chief executive officer of the daily, stressed Iliescu's contributions to the EU integration progress and the country's NATO membership invitation. (Nine o'Clock, Rompres - 23/01/03)
